WELD-1802 RequestScopedCache - Make sure each request is
 ended before a new one is started

Here is the root cause:
The bug was caused by the failure to properly end a previous request before starting a new one, which could lead to overlapping requests and inconsistent state in the request-scoped cache. This situation arises when the `beginRequest()` method is called without ensuring that the previous request has been concluded, potentially leaving stale data in the cache.

